# hexa-lang /.roadmap — created 2026-04-26
# Re-introduced after 2026-04-25 retire (commit 3caebc54). Scope is
# narrow on purpose: hexa-lang-internal compiler/runtime work that
# does not belong in hive's SSOT. Cross-repo coordination still flows
# through hive/.roadmap.

# scope
#   hexa-lang = self-hosted compiler + runtime + stdlib.
#   This file tracks compiler/runtime ROI work; agent/UX/swarm work
#   belongs in hive. Per-repo SSOT files were retired 2026-04-25 in
#   favor of hive-as-sole-source, but compiler-internal initiatives
#   (toolchain, codegen backends, perf wedges) accumulated locally
#   without a registry — this file restores that registry only for
#   hexa-lang-internal scope.

# baseline (2026-04-26, post perf-32 + 02af1622 + 132d1e17 + 5401409e)
#   tool/changelog_parse.hexa cold aot_build_slot profile (16KB flat):
#     module_loader flatten   215ms   7%
#     hexa_v2 transpile        26ms   1%   (was 2,192ms pre-02af1622)
#     clang -O2 link        1,600ms  84%  ← dominant
#     other                  ~250ms   8%
#   hexa_full.hexa (753KB) transpile: 631ms.
#   codegen_c2.hexa (280KB) transpile: 147ms.
#   Conclusion: clang link is now the bottleneck on every cold compile
#   and every runtime.c edit invalidation.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# active entries
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- partial [SH1] self-host AOT — reduce/remove clang dependency
  status (2026-04-26):
    - Stage A survey done (commit 008061b3 + 3921d4c9). self/codegen/
      ships ARM64 + x86_64 + ELF + Mach-O + regalloc + peephole +
      liveness — all working in isolation. self/codegen_native.hexa
      (1062 LOC) + self/codegen_native_elf.hexa (417 LOC) +
      self/compile_pipeline.hexa (801 LOC) emit runnable native
      binaries from HARDCODED ASTs but lack a frontend bridge from
      hexa-source → IR → these emitters. clang is the link backend
      hardcoded at self/main.hexa:1709.
    - Stage B W1 shipped (3921d4c9): HEXA_AOT_CC env toggle in
      aot_build_slot. Default "clang" preserves baseline (zero
      regression). Backend identity folded into cflag_str → link_key
      so swapping invalidates the cache cleanly.
    - Stage C W1-zig witness FAILED ≥30% gate: trivial cold
      ~3.17s clang vs ~5.49s zig cc on system load 11+; zig cc
      shows no advantage on hexa-generated 12K-LOC C TU (clang is
      already LLVM-tuned for this shape). Same-binary same-cache-state
      runs varied ±50% under high load — reliable 30% measurement
      requires a quieter runner.
    - Stage B W2/W3 found NOT to be single-wedge work: W2 (runtime.o
      split) requires codegen_c2.hexa to stop emitting `#include
      "runtime.c"` plus a runtime.h extern surface; W3 (direct
      native) requires a hexa-source → IR frontend which neither
      codegen_native.hexa nor compile_pipeline.hexa currently ship.
    - limit-witness: compute-saturation on a single-wedge
      cc-substitution (clang already saturates LLVM optimization
      cost on this TU shape; further cc-swap gains capped <30%).
      A real ≥30%+ requires either runtime.c TU split (W2) or
      backend rewire to native emitters (W3) — both multi-day.
    - W1 dispatch surface KEPT: 0 regression, future backends can
      ride this entry point (planned: tool/aot_cc_select.hexa once
      a non-clang backend lands).
  follow-ups (split out as new entries below):
    SH2 — runtime.c TU split + .o-cache (W2 done properly)
    SH3 — frontend bridge: hexa-AST → compile_pipeline IR (unblocks
          W3/W4, the actual self-hosting wedges)
  goal:
    - per README "Self-hosted 100% .hexa" + ARM64/x86_64 target claims,
      current path is hexa → C → clang → native; aim is hexa →
      ARM64/x86_64 directly (or via cached object lib + faster cc).
  acceptance:
    - cold aot_build_slot ≥30% faster on tool/changelog_parse.hexa
    - byte-identical (or behaviourally identical) output vs baseline
    - all four bench targets (cold, warm, multi-use, trivial) measured
  stages:
    A) survey — self/native/, self/aarch64*/arm64*/codegen*/asm*/elf*/
       macho*/linker*/jit*, tool/build_native.hexa + other build scripts,
       README targets vs wired, bench/native, inter-repo (anima, nexus,
       n6-architecture, airgenome). Output: maturity table + blockers.
    B) wedge — pick smallest viable (highest "shipped/LOC"):
       W1 faster cc (clang→tcc/zig cc) via HEXA_AOT_CC env toggle
       W2 cached runtime.o object lib (verify _layers/link/ doesn't
          already cover; coordinate with Agent 3's 132d1e17 cache)
       W3 direct ARM64 codegen for trivial scripts + system `as`,
          fall back to clang for non-trivial — first real self-host
       W4 revive whatever survey turns up, if mature enough
    C) witness — bench 4 targets vs commit 02af1622 baseline:
       (1) tool/changelog_parse.hexa cold (clean cache)
       (2) same warm
       (3) tool/blocker_autofire.hexa (multi-use)
       (4) trivial println("hi") — worst case for clang fixed overhead
       Both correctness (byte/behaviour identical) and speed (≥30%).
  don't-touch (parallel-agent settled territory):
    - self/runtime.c              (perf-32 settled)
    - self/main.hexa              (Agent 3 layered cache; coordinate
                                   if a wedge enters aot_build_slot)
    - build/hexa_interp shim      (Agent 2 settled)
    - self/native/hexa_cc.c L1    (Agent 4 setenv)
    - hive/, anima/, nexus/       (read-only)
  do-touch:
    - new self/native/ codegen modules
    - tool/build_*.hexa (where wedge demands)
    - new tool/aot_cc_select.hexa (backend selector, if W1)
    - README.md targets section (only if a real backend ships)
  build-cycle:
    - hexa build self/main.hexa <out> → build/artifacts/app
    - replacing live /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/hexa REQUIRES
      `codesign --sign - --force /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/hexa`
      else macOS Gatekeeper SIGKILLs second invocation.
  exit-on-witness:
    - omega cycle: if wedge moves cold-compile <30%, that IS the
      witness — don't ship a "self-hosting" win that's slower than
      baseline. Document the blocker and surface next wedge.
  on-completion:
    - commit prefix: `feat(self-host):` or `perf(aot-cc):`
    - body must include: Stage A survey table + chosen wedge +
      rationale + Stage C measurements
    - update memory: project_hexa_perf32_aot_use_resolution.md OR
      new project_hexa_self_hosting_progress.md (if scope large)
    - document remaining clang surface + follow-up wedges
  related-memory:
    - /Users/ghost/.claude/projects/-Users-ghost-core-hive/memory/
      project_hexa_perf32_aot_use_resolution.md
    - /Users/ghost/.claude/projects/-Users-ghost-core-hive/memory/
      project_omega_saturation_cycle.md

- todo [SH2] runtime.c TU split + cached runtime.o (real W2)
  goal:
    - Stop codegen_c2.hexa from emitting `#include "runtime.c"`. Replace
      with `#include "runtime.h"` (extern decl surface). Pre-compile
      runtime.c → runtime.o once per (cflag, uname) tuple, cache under
      .hexa-cache/_layers/runtime_o/<key>.o. Link script.o against the
      cached runtime.o instead of recompiling 11K LOC of runtime per
      script.
  acceptance:
    - cold aot_build_slot ≥30% faster on tool/changelog_parse.hexa
      under quiet load (load avg <2)
    - byte/behaviour identical output vs current pipeline
    - cache invalidation on runtime.c content change still works
      (already covered by src_fingerprint_deep)
  blockers:
    - codegen_c2.hexa emit pattern change (include + extern surface)
    - runtime.h extraction (auto-generate or hand-curate from runtime.c)
    - main.hexa link step: 1-shot clang → 2-shot (compile + link)
    - benchmark must run on a quiet machine (load <2) or noise dominates
  related:
    - SH1 W1 dispatch surface (HEXA_AOT_CC) reused as backend selector
    - Agent 3 132d1e17 layered cache pattern (mirrors per-key promote)

- todo [SH3] hexa-AST → compile_pipeline IR frontend bridge
  goal:
    - The actual self-hosting wedge. self/compile_pipeline.hexa already
      lowers IR → ARM64 bytes; self/codegen_native.hexa emits Mach-O.
      What's missing is the front: hexa-source → AST → IR. Build that
      bridge so a trivial subset of hexa (literals + arith + control
      flow + syscall write/exit) can compile WITHOUT clang. Expand the
      subset incrementally; fall back to clang for everything else.
  acceptance:
    - trivial println("hi") cold compile fully self-hosted (no clang
      anywhere), ≥30% faster than W0 baseline on quiet load
    - automatic fallback to clang for non-supported nodes — zero
      regression on changelog_parse / blocker_autofire (which use
      stdlib + complex control flow)
    - HEXA_AOT_CC=native (or HEXA_AOT_BACKEND=native) routes through
      the bridge; default still clang
  blockers:
    - frontend AST is the hexa_v2 transpiler's internal shape;
      compile_pipeline expects a different IRInstr/IRBlock shape
      (see self/compile_pipeline.hexa:130-185). Need an adapter.
    - runtime ABI: hexa heap values use HexaVal tagged union; native
      emitters currently work in raw ints. Need either a tag-aware
      lowering or a "trivial-only" gate that rejects HexaVal-touching
      programs and falls back to clang.
  related:
    - bench/native (TBD) — micro-benches of pure-native trivial cases
    - codegen_native.hexa standalone demo binary (already passes 6/6
      hardcoded-AST tests; same ARM64 path, different frontend)

